284 void MipsTargetStreamer::emitEmptyDelaySlot(bool hasShortDelaySlot, SMLoc IDLoc, 0
285 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) { ----
286 // The default case of `nop` is `sll $zero, $zero, 0`. ----
287 unsigned Opc = Mips::SLL; 0
288 if (isMicroMips(STI) && hasShortDelaySlot) { 0
289 Opc = isMips32r6(STI) ? Mips::MOVE16_MMR6 : Mips::MOVE16_MM; 0
290 emitRR(Opc, Mips::ZERO, Mips::ZERO, IDLoc, STI); 0
291 return; 0
292 } ----
293 ----
294 if (isMicroMips(STI)) 0
295 Opc = isMips32r6(STI) ? Mips::SLL_MMR6 : Mips::SLL_MM; 0
296 ----
297 emitRRI(Opc, Mips::ZERO, Mips::ZERO, 0, IDLoc, STI); 0
298 } ----
299 ----
300 void MipsTargetStreamer::emitNop(SMLoc IDLoc, const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) { 0
301 if (isMicroMips(STI)) 0
302 emitRR(Mips::MOVE16_MM, Mips::ZERO, Mips::ZERO, IDLoc, STI); 0
303 else ----
304 emitRRI(Mips::SLL, Mips::ZERO, Mips::ZERO, 0, IDLoc, STI); 0
305 } 0

307 /// Emit the $gp restore operation for .cprestore. ----
308 void MipsTargetStreamer::emitGPRestore(int Offset, SMLoc IDLoc, 0
309 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) { ----
310 emitLoadWithImmOffset(Mips::LW, GPReg, Mips::SP, Offset, GPReg, IDLoc, STI); 0
311 } 0
312 ----
313 /// Emit a store instruction with an immediate offset. ----
314 void MipsTargetStreamer::emitStoreWithImmOffset( 0
315 unsigned Opcode, unsigned SrcReg, unsigned BaseReg, int64_t Offset, ----
316 function_ref GetATReg, SMLoc IDLoc, ----
317 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) { ----
318 if (isInt<16>(Offset)) { 0
319 emitRRI(Opcode, SrcReg, BaseReg, Offset, IDLoc, STI); 0
320 return; 0
321 } ----
322 ----
323 // sw $8, offset($8) => lui $at, %hi(offset) ----
324 // add $at, $at, $8 ----
325 // sw $8, %lo(offset)($at) ----
326 ----
327 unsigned ATReg = GetATReg(); 0
328 if (!ATReg) 0
329 return; 0
330 ----
331 unsigned LoOffset = Offset & 0x0000ffff; 0
332 unsigned HiOffset = (Offset & 0xffff0000) >> 16; 0
333 ----
334 // If msb of LoOffset is 1(negative number) we must increment HiOffset ----
335 // to account for the sign-extension of the low part. ----
336 if (LoOffset & 0x8000) 0
337 HiOffset++; 0
338 ----
339 // Generate the base address in ATReg. ----
340 emitRI(Mips::LUi, ATReg, HiOffset, IDLoc, STI); 0
341 if (BaseReg != Mips::ZERO) 0
342 emitRRR(Mips::ADDu, ATReg, ATReg, BaseReg, IDLoc, STI); 0
343 // Emit the store with the adjusted base and offset. ----
344 emitRRI(Opcode, SrcReg, ATReg, LoOffset, IDLoc, STI); 0
345 } ----
346 ----
347 /// Emit a load instruction with an immediate offset. DstReg and TmpReg are ----
348 /// permitted to be the same register iff DstReg is distinct from BaseReg and ----
349 /// DstReg is a GPR. It is the callers responsibility to identify such cases ----
350 /// and pass the appropriate register in TmpReg. ----
351 void MipsTargetStreamer::emitLoadWithImmOffset(unsigned Opcode, unsigned DstReg, 0
352 unsigned BaseReg, int64_t Offset, ----
353 unsigned TmpReg, SMLoc IDLoc, ----
354 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) { ----
355 if (isInt<16>(Offset)) { 0
356 emitRRI(Opcode, DstReg, BaseReg, Offset, IDLoc, STI); 0
357 return; 0
358 } ----
359 ----
360 // 1) lw $8, offset($9) => lui $8, %hi(offset) ----
361 // add $8, $8, $9 ----
362 // lw $8, %lo(offset)($9) ----
363 // 2) lw $8, offset($8) => lui $at, %hi(offset) ----
364 // add $at, $at, $8 ----
365 // lw $8, %lo(offset)($at) ----
366 ----
367 unsigned LoOffset = Offset & 0x0000ffff; 0
368 unsigned HiOffset = (Offset & 0xffff0000) >> 16; 0
369 ----
370 // If msb of LoOffset is 1(negative number) we must increment HiOffset ----
371 // to account for the sign-extension of the low part. ----
372 if (LoOffset & 0x8000) 0
373 HiOffset++; 0
374 ----
375 // Generate the base address in TmpReg. ----
376 emitRI(Mips::LUi, TmpReg, HiOffset, IDLoc, STI); 0
377 if (BaseReg != Mips::ZERO) 0
378 emitRRR(Mips::ADDu, TmpReg, TmpReg, BaseReg, IDLoc, STI); 0
379 // Emit the load with the adjusted base and offset. ----
380 emitRRI(Opcode, DstReg, TmpReg, LoOffset, IDLoc, STI); 0
381 } ----

660 static void printHex32(unsigned Value, raw_ostream &OS) { 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
661 OS << "0x"; 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
662 for (int i = 7; i >= 0; i--) 36 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
663 OS.write_hex((Value & (0xF << (i * 4))) >> (i * 4)); 32 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
664 } 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll

798 ----
799 // This part is for ELF object output. ----
800 MipsTargetELFStreamer::MipsTargetELFStreamer(MCStreamer &S, 0
801 const MCSubtargetInfo &STI) ----
802 : MipsTargetStreamer(S), MicroMipsEnabled(false), STI(STI) { 0
803 MCAssembler &MCA = getStreamer().getAssembler(); 0
804 ----
805 // It's possible that MCObjectFileInfo isn't fully initialized at this point ----
806 // due to an initialization order problem where LLVMTargetMachine creates the ----
807 // target streamer before TargetLoweringObjectFile calls ----
808 // InitializeMCObjectFileInfo. There doesn't seem to be a single place that ----
809 // covers all cases so this statement covers most cases and direct object ----
810 // emission must call setPic() once MCObjectFileInfo has been initialized. The ----
811 // cases we don't handle here are covered by MipsAsmPrinter. ----
812 Pic = MCA.getContext().getObjectFileInfo()->isPositionIndependent(); 0
813 ----
814 const FeatureBitset &Features = STI.getFeatureBits(); 0
815 ----
816 // Set the header flags that we can in the constructor. ----
817 // FIXME: This is a fairly terrible hack. We set the rest ----
818 // of these in the destructor. The problem here is two-fold: ----
819 // ----
820 // a: Some of the eflags can be set/reset by directives. ----
821 // b: There aren't any usage paths that initialize the ABI ----
822 // pointer until after we initialize either an assembler ----
823 // or the target machine. ----
824 // We can fix this by making the target streamer construct ----
825 // the ABI, but this is fraught with wide ranging dependency ----
826 // issues as well. ----
827 unsigned EFlags = MCA.getELFHeaderEFlags(); 0
828 ----
829 // FIXME: Fix a dependency issue by instantiating the ABI object to some ----
830 // default based off the triple. The triple doesn't describe the target ----
831 // fully, but any external user of the API that uses the MCTargetStreamer ----
832 // would otherwise crash on assertion failure. ----
833 ----
834 ABI = MipsABIInfo( 0
835 STI.getTargetTriple().getArch() == Triple::ArchType::mipsel || 0
836 STI.getTargetTriple().getArch() == Triple::ArchType::mips 0
837 ? MipsABIInfo::O32() 0
838 : MipsABIInfo::N64()); 0
839 ----
840 // Architecture ----
841 if (Features[Mips::FeatureMips64r6]) 0
842 EFlags |= ELF::EF_MIPS_ARCH_64R6; 0
843 else if (Features[Mips::FeatureMips64r2] || 0
844 Features[Mips::FeatureMips64r3] || 0
845 Features[Mips::FeatureMips64r5]) 0
846 EFlags |= ELF::EF_MIPS_ARCH_64R2; 0
847 else if (Features[Mips::FeatureMips64]) 0
848 EFlags |= ELF::EF_MIPS_ARCH_64; 0
849 else if (Features[Mips::FeatureMips5]) 0
850 EFlags |= ELF::EF_MIPS_ARCH_5; 0
851 else if (Features[Mips::FeatureMips4]) 0
852 EFlags |= ELF::EF_MIPS_ARCH_4; 0
853 else if (Features[Mips::FeatureMips3]) 0
854 EFlags |= ELF::EF_MIPS_ARCH_3; 0
855 else if (Features[Mips::FeatureMips32r6]) 0
856 EFlags |= ELF::EF_MIPS_ARCH_32R6; 0
857 else if (Features[Mips::FeatureMips32r2] || 0
858 Features[Mips::FeatureMips32r3] || 0
859 Features[Mips::FeatureMips32r5]) 0
860 EFlags |= ELF::EF_MIPS_ARCH_32R2; 0
861 else if (Features[Mips::FeatureMips32]) 0
862 EFlags |= ELF::EF_MIPS_ARCH_32; 0
863 else if (Features[Mips::FeatureMips2]) 0
864 EFlags |= ELF::EF_MIPS_ARCH_2; 0
865 else ----
866 EFlags |= ELF::EF_MIPS_ARCH_1; 0
867 ----
868 // Machine ----
869 if (Features[Mips::FeatureCnMips]) 0
870 EFlags |= ELF::EF_MIPS_MACH_OCTEON; 0
871 ----
872 // Other options. ----
873 if (Features[Mips::FeatureNaN2008]) 0
874 EFlags |= ELF::EF_MIPS_NAN2008; 0
875 ----
876 MCA.setELFHeaderEFlags(EFlags); 0
877 } 0
878 ----
879 void MipsTargetELFStreamer::emitLabel(MCSymbol *S) { 0
880 auto *Symbol = cast(S); 0
881 getStreamer().getAssembler().registerSymbol(*Symbol); 0
882 uint8_t Type = Symbol->getType(); 0
883 if (Type != ELF::STT_FUNC) 0
884 return; 0
885 ----
886 if (isMicroMipsEnabled()) 0
887 Symbol->setOther(ELF::STO_MIPS_MICROMIPS); 0
888 } ----
889 ----
890 void MipsTargetELFStreamer::finish() { 0
891 MCAssembler &MCA = getStreamer().getAssembler(); 0
892 const MCObjectFileInfo &OFI = *MCA.getContext().getObjectFileInfo(); 0
893 ----
894 // .bss, .text and .data are always at least 16-byte aligned. ----
895 MCSection &TextSection = *OFI.getTextSection(); 0
896 MCA.registerSection(TextSection); 0
897 MCSection &DataSection = *OFI.getDataSection(); 0
898 MCA.registerSection(DataSection); 0
899 MCSection &BSSSection = *OFI.getBSSSection(); 0
900 MCA.registerSection(BSSSection); 0
901 ----
902 TextSection.ensureMinAlignment(Align(16)); 0
903 DataSection.ensureMinAlignment(Align(16)); 0
904 BSSSection.ensureMinAlignment(Align(16)); 0
905 ----
906 if (RoundSectionSizes) { 0
907 // Make sections sizes a multiple of the alignment. This is useful for ----
908 // verifying the output of IAS against the output of other assemblers but ----
909 // it's not necessary to produce a correct object and increases section ----
910 // size. ----
911 MCStreamer &OS = getStreamer(); 0
912 for (MCSection &S : MCA) { 0
913 MCSectionELF &Section = static_cast(S); 0
914 ----
915 Align Alignment = Section.getAlign(); 0
916 OS.switchSection(&Section); 0
917 if (Section.useCodeAlign()) 0
918 OS.emitCodeAlignment(Alignment, &STI, Alignment.value()); 0
919 else ----
920 OS.emitValueToAlignment(Alignment, 0, 1, Alignment.value()); 0
921 } ----
922 } ----
923 ----
924 const FeatureBitset &Features = STI.getFeatureBits(); 0
925 ----
926 // Update e_header flags. See the FIXME and comment above in ----
927 // the constructor for a full rundown on this. ----
928 unsigned EFlags = MCA.getELFHeaderEFlags(); 0
929 ----
930 // ABI ----
931 // N64 does not require any ABI bits. ----
932 if (getABI().IsO32()) 0
933 EFlags |= ELF::EF_MIPS_ABI_O32; 0
934 else if (getABI().IsN32()) 0
935 EFlags |= ELF::EF_MIPS_ABI2; 0
936 ----
937 if (Features[Mips::FeatureGP64Bit]) { 0
938 if (getABI().IsO32()) 0
939 EFlags |= ELF::EF_MIPS_32BITMODE; /* Compatibility Mode */ 0
940 } else if (Features[Mips::FeatureMips64r2] || Features[Mips::FeatureMips64]) 0
941 EFlags |= ELF::EF_MIPS_32BITMODE; 0
942 ----
943 // -mplt is not implemented but we should act as if it was ----
944 // given. ----
945 if (!Features[Mips::FeatureNoABICalls]) 0
946 EFlags |= ELF::EF_MIPS_CPIC; 0
947 ----
948 if (Pic) 0

1012 ----
1013 void MipsTargetELFStreamer::emitDirectiveEnd(StringRef Name) { 0
1014 MCAssembler &MCA = getStreamer().getAssembler(); 0
1015 MCContext &Context = MCA.getContext(); 0
1016 MCStreamer &OS = getStreamer(); 0
1017 ----
1018 MCSectionELF *Sec = Context.getELFSection(".pdr", ELF::SHT_PROGBITS, 0); 0
1019 ----
1020 MCSymbol *Sym = Context.getOrCreateSymbol(Name); 0
1021 const MCSymbolRefExpr *ExprRef = ----
1022 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Sym, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, Context); 0
1023 ----
1024 MCA.registerSection(*Sec); 0
1025 Sec->setAlignment(Align(4)); 0
1026 ----
1027 OS.pushSection(); 0
1028 ----
1029 OS.switchSection(Sec); 0
1030 ----
1031 OS.emitValueImpl(ExprRef, 4); 0
1032 ----
1033 OS.emitIntValue(GPRInfoSet ? GPRBitMask : 0, 4); // reg_mask 0
1034 OS.emitIntValue(GPRInfoSet ? GPROffset : 0, 4); // reg_offset 0
1035 ----
1036 OS.emitIntValue(FPRInfoSet ? FPRBitMask : 0, 4); // fpreg_mask 0
1037 OS.emitIntValue(FPRInfoSet ? FPROffset : 0, 4); // fpreg_offset 0
1038 ----
1039 OS.emitIntValue(FrameInfoSet ? FrameOffset : 0, 4); // frame_offset 0
1040 OS.emitIntValue(FrameInfoSet ? FrameReg : 0, 4); // frame_reg 0
1041 OS.emitIntValue(FrameInfoSet ? ReturnReg : 0, 4); // return_reg 0
1042 ----
1043 // The .end directive marks the end of a procedure. Invalidate ----
1044 // the information gathered up until this point. ----
1045 GPRInfoSet = FPRInfoSet = FrameInfoSet = false; 0
1046 ----
1047 OS.popSection(); 0
1048 ----
1049 // .end also implicitly sets the size. ----
1050 MCSymbol *CurPCSym = Context.createTempSymbol(); 0
1051 OS.emitLabel(CurPCSym); 0
1052 const MCExpr *Size = MCBinaryExpr::createSub( 0
1053 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(CurPCSym, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, Context), 0
1054 ExprRef, Context); ----
1055 ----
1056 // The ELFObjectWriter can determine the absolute size as it has access to ----
1057 // the layout information of the assembly file, so a size expression rather ----
1058 // than an absolute value is ok here. ----
1059 static_cast(Sym)->setSize(Size); 0
1060 } 0

1152 ----
1153 void MipsTargetELFStreamer::emitDirectiveCpLoad(unsigned RegNo) { 0
1154 // .cpload $reg ----
1155 // This directive expands to: ----
1156 // lui $gp, %hi(_gp_disp) ----
1157 // addui $gp, $gp, %lo(_gp_disp) ----
1158 // addu $gp, $gp, $reg ----
1159 // when support for position independent code is enabled. ----
1160 if (!Pic || (getABI().IsN32() || getABI().IsN64())) 0
1161 return; 0
1162 ----
1163 // There's a GNU extension controlled by -mno-shared that allows ----
1164 // locally-binding symbols to be accessed using absolute addresses. ----
1165 // This is currently not supported. When supported -mno-shared makes ----
1166 // .cpload expand to: ----
1167 // lui $gp, %hi(__gnu_local_gp) ----
1168 // addiu $gp, $gp, %lo(__gnu_local_gp) ----
1169 ----
1170 StringRef SymName("_gp_disp"); 0
1171 MCAssembler &MCA = getStreamer().getAssembler(); 0
1172 MCSymbol *GP_Disp = MCA.getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(SymName); 0
1173 MCA.registerSymbol(*GP_Disp); 0
1174 ----
1175 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1176 TmpInst.setOpcode(Mips::LUi); 0
1177 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(GPReg)); 0
1178 const MCExpr *HiSym = MipsMCExpr::create( 0
1179 MipsMCExpr::MEK_HI, ----
1180 MCSymbolRefExpr::create("_gp_disp", MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, 0
1181 MCA.getContext()), ----
1182 MCA.getContext()); 0
1183 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(HiSym)); 0
1184 getStreamer().emitInstruction(TmpInst, STI); 0
1185 ----
1186 TmpInst.clear(); 0
1187 ----
1188 TmpInst.setOpcode(Mips::ADDiu); 0
1189 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(GPReg)); 0
1190 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(GPReg)); 0
1191 const MCExpr *LoSym = MipsMCExpr::create( 0
1192 MipsMCExpr::MEK_LO, ----
1193 MCSymbolRefExpr::create("_gp_disp", MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, 0
1194 MCA.getContext()), ----
1195 MCA.getContext()); 0
1196 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(LoSym)); 0
1197 getStreamer().emitInstruction(TmpInst, STI); 0
1198 ----
1199 TmpInst.clear(); 0
1200 ----
1201 TmpInst.setOpcode(Mips::ADDu); 0
1202 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(GPReg)); 0
1203 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(GPReg)); 0
1204 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(RegNo)); 0
1205 getStreamer().emitInstruction(TmpInst, STI); 0
1206 ----
1207 forbidModuleDirective(); 0
1208 } 0

1214 ----
1215 bool MipsTargetELFStreamer::emitDirectiveCpRestore( 0
1216 int Offset, function_ref GetATReg, SMLoc IDLoc, ----
1217 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) { ----
1218 MipsTargetStreamer::emitDirectiveCpRestore(Offset, GetATReg, IDLoc, STI); 0
1219 // .cprestore offset ----
1220 // When PIC mode is enabled and the O32 ABI is used, this directive expands ----
1221 // to: ----
1222 // sw $gp, offset($sp) ----
1223 // and adds a corresponding LW after every JAL. ----
1224 ----
1225 // Note that .cprestore is ignored if used with the N32 and N64 ABIs or if it ----
1226 // is used in non-PIC mode. ----
1227 if (!Pic || (getABI().IsN32() || getABI().IsN64())) 0
1228 return true; 0
1229 ----
1230 // Store the $gp on the stack. ----
1231 emitStoreWithImmOffset(Mips::SW, GPReg, Mips::SP, Offset, GetATReg, IDLoc, 0
1232 STI); ----
1233 return true; 0
1234 } ----
1235 ----
1236 void MipsTargetELFStreamer::emitDirectiveCpsetup(unsigned RegNo, 0
1237 int RegOrOffset, ----
1238 const MCSymbol &Sym, ----
1239 bool IsReg) { ----
1240 // Only N32 and N64 emit anything for .cpsetup iff PIC is set. ----
1241 if (!Pic || !(getABI().IsN32() || getABI().IsN64())) 0
1242 return; 0
1243 ----
1244 forbidModuleDirective(); 0
1245 ----
1246 MCAssembler &MCA = getStreamer().getAssembler(); 0
1247 MCInst Inst; 0
1248 ----
1249 // Either store the old $gp in a register or on the stack ----
1250 if (IsReg) { 0
1251 // move $save, $gpreg ----
1252 emitRRR(Mips::OR64, RegOrOffset, GPReg, Mips::ZERO, SMLoc(), &STI); 0
1253 } else { ----
1254 // sd $gpreg, offset($sp) ----
1255 emitRRI(Mips::SD, GPReg, Mips::SP, RegOrOffset, SMLoc(), &STI); 0
1256 } ----
1257 ----
1258 if (getABI().IsN32()) { 0
1259 MCSymbol *GPSym = MCA.getContext().getOrCreateSymbol("__gnu_local_gp"); 0
1260 const MipsMCExpr *HiExpr = MipsMCExpr::create( 0
1261 MipsMCExpr::MEK_HI, MCSymbolRefExpr::create(GPSym, MCA.getContext()), 0
1262 MCA.getContext()); ----
1263 const MipsMCExpr *LoExpr = MipsMCExpr::create( 0
1264 MipsMCExpr::MEK_LO, MCSymbolRefExpr::create(GPSym, MCA.getContext()), 0
1265 MCA.getContext()); ----
1266 ----
1267 // lui $gp, %hi(__gnu_local_gp) ----
1268 emitRX(Mips::LUi, GPReg, MCOperand::createExpr(HiExpr), SMLoc(), &STI); 0
1269 ----
1270 // addiu $gp, $gp, %lo(__gnu_local_gp) ----
1271 emitRRX(Mips::ADDiu, GPReg, GPReg, MCOperand::createExpr(LoExpr), SMLoc(), 0
1272 &STI); 0
1273 ----
1274 return; 0
1275 } ----
1276 ----
1277 const MipsMCExpr *HiExpr = MipsMCExpr::createGpOff( 0
1278 MipsMCExpr::MEK_HI, MCSymbolRefExpr::create(&Sym, MCA.getContext()), 0
1279 MCA.getContext()); ----
1280 const MipsMCExpr *LoExpr = MipsMCExpr::createGpOff( 0
1281 MipsMCExpr::MEK_LO, MCSymbolRefExpr::create(&Sym, MCA.getContext()), 0
1282 MCA.getContext()); ----
1283 ----
1284 // lui $gp, %hi(%neg(%gp_rel(funcSym))) ----
1285 emitRX(Mips::LUi, GPReg, MCOperand::createExpr(HiExpr), SMLoc(), &STI); 0
1286 ----
1287 // addiu $gp, $gp, %lo(%neg(%gp_rel(funcSym))) ----
1288 emitRRX(Mips::ADDiu, GPReg, GPReg, MCOperand::createExpr(LoExpr), SMLoc(), 0
1289 &STI); 0
1290 ----
1291 // daddu $gp, $gp, $funcreg ----
1292 emitRRR(Mips::DADDu, GPReg, GPReg, RegNo, SMLoc(), &STI); 0
1293 } 0
1294 ----
1295 void MipsTargetELFStreamer::emitDirectiveCpreturn(unsigned SaveLocation, 0
1296 bool SaveLocationIsRegister) { ----
1297 // Only N32 and N64 emit anything for .cpreturn iff PIC is set. ----
1298 if (!Pic || !(getABI().IsN32() || getABI().IsN64())) 0
1299 return; 0
1300 ----
1301 MCInst Inst; 0
1302 // Either restore the old $gp from a register or on the stack ----
1303 if (SaveLocationIsRegister) { 0
1304 Inst.setOpcode(Mips::OR); 0
1305 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(GPReg)); 0
1306 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(SaveLocation)); 0
1307 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Mips::ZERO)); 0
1308 } else { ----
1309 Inst.setOpcode(Mips::LD); 0
1310 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(GPReg)); 0
1311 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Mips::SP)); 0
1312 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(SaveLocation)); 0
1313 } ----
1314 getStreamer().emitInstruction(Inst, STI); 0
1315 ----
1316 forbidModuleDirective(); 0
1317 } 0

314 void MipsTargetStreamer::emitStoreWithImmOffset( 314 void MipsTargetStreamer::emitStoreWithImmOffset(
315 unsigned Opcode, unsigned SrcReg, unsigned BaseReg, int64_t Offset, 315 unsigned Opcode, unsigned SrcReg, unsigned BaseReg, int64_t Offset,
316 function_ref GetATReg, SMLoc IDLoc, 316 function_ref GetATReg, SMLoc IDLoc,
317 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) { 317 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
318 if (isInt<16>(Offset)) { 318 if (isInt<16>(Offset)) {

322 322
323 // sw $8, offset($8) => lui $at, %hi(offset) 323 // sw $8, offset($8) => lui $at, %hi(offset)
324 // add $at, $at, $8 324 // add $at, $at, $8
325 // sw $8, %lo(offset)($at) 325 // sw $8, %lo(offset)($at)
326 326
327 unsigned ATReg = GetATReg(); 327 unsigned ATReg = GetATReg();
328 if (!ATReg) 328 if (!ATReg)
329 return; 329 return;
330 330
331 unsigned LoOffset = Offset & 0x0000ffff; 331 unsigned LoOffset = Offset & 0x0000ffff;
332 unsigned HiOffset = (Offset & 0xffff0000) >> 16; 332 unsigned HiOffset = (Offset & 0xffff0000) >> 16;
333 333
334 // If msb of LoOffset is 1(negative number) we must increment HiOffset 334 // If msb of LoOffset is 1(negative number) we must increment HiOffset
335 // to account for the sign-extension of the low part. 335 // to account for the sign-extension of the low part.
336 if (LoOffset & 0x8000) 336 if (LoOffset & 0x8000)
337 HiOffset++; 337 HiOffset++;
338 338
339 // Generate the base address in ATReg. 339 // Generate the base address in ATReg.
340 emitRI(Mips::LUi, ATReg, HiOffset, IDLoc, STI); 340 emitRI(Mips::LUi, ATReg, HiOffset, IDLoc, STI);
341 if (BaseReg != Mips::ZERO) 341 if (BaseReg != Mips::ZERO)
342 emitRRR(Mips::ADDu, ATReg, ATReg, BaseReg, IDLoc, STI); 342 emitRRR(Mips::ADDu, ATReg, ATReg, BaseReg, IDLoc, STI);
343 // Emit the store with the adjusted base and offset. 343 // Emit the store with the adjusted base and offset.
344 emitRRI(Opcode, SrcReg, ATReg, LoOffset, IDLoc, STI); 344 emitRRI(Opcode, SrcReg, ATReg, LoOffset, IDLoc, STI);
345 } 345 }

347 /// Emit a load instruction with an immediate offset. DstReg and TmpReg are 347 /// Emit a load instruction with an immediate offset. DstReg and TmpReg are
348 /// permitted to be the same register iff DstReg is distinct from BaseReg and 348 /// permitted to be the same register iff DstReg is distinct from BaseReg and
349 /// DstReg is a GPR. It is the callers responsibility to identify such cases 349 /// DstReg is a GPR. It is the callers responsibility to identify such cases
350 /// and pass the appropriate register in TmpReg. 350 /// and pass the appropriate register in TmpReg.
351 void MipsTargetStreamer::emitLoadWithImmOffset(unsigned Opcode, unsigned DstReg, 351 void MipsTargetStreamer::emitLoadWithImmOffset(unsigned Opcode, unsigned DstReg,
352 unsigned BaseReg, int64_t Offset, 352 unsigned BaseReg, int64_t Offset,
353 unsigned TmpReg, SMLoc IDLoc, 353 unsigned TmpReg, SMLoc IDLoc,
354 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) { 354 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
355 if (isInt<16>(Offset)) { 355 if (isInt<16>(Offset)) {
356 emitRRI(Opcode, DstReg, BaseReg, Offset, IDLoc, STI); 356 emitRRI(Opcode, DstReg, BaseReg, Offset, IDLoc, STI);
357 return; 357 return;
358 } 358 }
359 359
360 // 1) lw $8, offset($9) => lui $8, %hi(offset) 360 // 1) lw $8, offset($9) => lui $8, %hi(offset)
361 // add $8, $8, $9 361 // add $8, $8, $9
362 // lw $8, %lo(offset)($9) 362 // lw $8, %lo(offset)($9)
363 // 2) lw $8, offset($8) => lui $at, %hi(offset) 363 // 2) lw $8, offset($8) => lui $at, %hi(offset)
364 // add $at, $at, $8 364 // add $at, $at, $8
365 // lw $8, %lo(offset)($at) 365 // lw $8, %lo(offset)($at)
366 366
367 unsigned LoOffset = Offset & 0x0000ffff; 367 unsigned LoOffset = Offset & 0x0000ffff;
368 unsigned HiOffset = (Offset & 0xffff0000) >> 16; 368 unsigned HiOffset = (Offset & 0xffff0000) >> 16;
369 369
370 // If msb of LoOffset is 1(negative number) we must increment HiOffset 370 // If msb of LoOffset is 1(negative number) we must increment HiOffset
371 // to account for the sign-extension of the low part. 371 // to account for the sign-extension of the low part.
372 if (LoOffset & 0x8000) 372 if (LoOffset & 0x8000)
373 HiOffset++; 373 HiOffset++;
374 374
375 // Generate the base address in TmpReg. 375 // Generate the base address in TmpReg.
376 emitRI(Mips::LUi, TmpReg, HiOffset, IDLoc, STI); 376 emitRI(Mips::LUi, TmpReg, HiOffset, IDLoc, STI);
377 if (BaseReg != Mips::ZERO) 377 if (BaseReg != Mips::ZERO)
378 emitRRR(Mips::ADDu, TmpReg, TmpReg, BaseReg, IDLoc, STI); 378 emitRRR(Mips::ADDu, TmpReg, TmpReg, BaseReg, IDLoc, STI);
379 // Emit the load with the adjusted base and offset. 379 // Emit the load with the adjusted base and offset.
380 emitRRI(Opcode, DstReg, TmpReg, LoOffset, IDLoc, STI); 380 emitRRI(Opcode, DstReg, TmpReg, LoOffset, IDLoc, STI);
381 } 381 }
